race.comment: GOLDEN WINGS (4) broke through with an easy maiden win by more than 4 lengths last start over 1200m at Ellerslie 18 days ago. He is lightly raced and still has more to give, so he can take the next step immediately. SPERLARI (12) wasn't far off when resuming, finishing fourth over 1200m at Ellerslie 4 weeks ago. She should appreciate the extra trip, and with that, run under the belt. She will be hard to hold out SISTA SUGAR (8) resumed with a strong effort for second over 1200m at Ellerslie after getting well back early on in the running. The extra furlong is key, and from a superior gate, she can go one better. MISTER MEANER (16) was a brave runner-up at Ellerslie in his penultimate start, and then was a close fifth over 1300m at Tauranga 3 weeks ago. Stick with him. SOCIAL CLIMBER (19) hasn't been firing this prep but might offer value in the betting as she steps up to 1400m for the first time. Don't risk her.
